 number of advertisements the company sent to its clients each year. It''s also given that x represents the number of years since 1997. Therefore, x equals 0 represents 0 years since 1997, or 1997. Thus, the best interpretation of the y-intercept of the graph of y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis is that the estimated number of advertisements the company sent to its clients in 1997 was 9,000.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-124", "text": "Triangle upper X upper Y upper Z is similar to triangle upper R upper S upper T such that upper X, upper Y, and upper Z correspond to upper R, upper S, and upper T, respectively. The measure of angle upper Z is 20 degree and 2 upper X upper Y equals upper R upper S. What is the measure of angle upper T?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["2 degree", "10 degree", "20 degree", "40 degree"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. It\u2019s given that triangle upper X upper Y upper Z is similar to triangle upper R upper S upper T, such that upper X, upper Y, and upper Z correspond to upper R, upper S, and upper T, respectively. Since corresponding angles of similar triangles are congruent, it follows that the measure of angle upper Z is congruent to the measure of angle upper T. It\u2019s given that the measure of angle upper Z is 20 degree. Therefore, the measure of angle upper T is 20 degree.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from a conceptual error.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is half the measure of angle upper Z.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is twice the measure of angle upper Z."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-131", "text": "f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 9 left parenthesis 4 right parenthesis Su