eptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the length of line segment upper E upper F, not line segment upper D upper E."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-187", "text": "Store A sells raspberries for dollar sign 5.50 per pint and blackberries for dollar sign 3.00 per pint. Store B sells raspberries for dollar sign 6.50 per pint and blackberries for dollar sign 8.00 per pint. A certain purchase of raspberries and blackberries would cost dollar sign 37.00 at Store A or dollar sign 66.00 at Store B. How many pints of blackberries are in this purchase?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["4", "5", "8", "12"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. It\u2019s given that store A sells raspberries for dollar sign 5 period 50 per pint and blackberries for dollar sign 3 period 00 per pint, and a certain purchase of raspberries and blackberries at store A would cost dollar sign 37 period 00. It\u2019s also given that store B sells raspberries for dollar sign 6 period 50 per pint and blackberries for dollar sign 8 period 00 per pint, and this purchase of raspberries and blackberries at store B would cost dollar sign 66 period 00. Let r represent the number of pints of raspberries and b represent the number of pints of blackberries in this purchase. The equation 5 period 50 r plus 3 period 00 b equals 37 period 00 represents this purchase of raspberries and blackberries from store A and the equation 6 period 50 r plus 8 period 00 b equals 66 period 00 represents this purchase of raspberries and blackberries from store B. Solving the system of equations by elimination gives the value of r and the value of b that make the system of equations true. Multiplying both sides of the equation for store A by 6.5 yields left parenthesis 5 period 50 r right parenthesis left parenthesis 6 period 5 right parenthesis plus left parenthesis 3 period 00 b right parenthesis left parenthesis 6 period 5 right parenthesis equals left parenthesis 37 period 00 right parenthesis left parenthesis 6 period 5 right parenthesis, or 35 period 75 r plus 19 period 5 b equals 240 period 5. Multiplying both sides of the equation for store B by 5.5 yields left parenthesis 6 period 50 r right parenthesis left parenthesis 5 period 5 right parenthesis plus left parenthesis 8 period 00 b right parenthesis left parenthesis 5 period 5 right parenthesis equals left parenthesis 66 period 00 right parenthesis left parenthesis 5 period 5 right parenthesis, or 35 period 75 r plus 44 b equals 363. Subtracting both sides of the equation for store A, 35 period 75 r plus 19 period 5 b equals 240 period 5, from the corresponding sides of the equation for store B, 35 period 75 r plus 44 b equals 363, yields left parenthesis 35 period 75 r minus 35 period 75 r right parenthesis plus left parenthesis 44 b minus 19 period 5 b right parenthesis equals left parenthesis 363 minus 240 period 5 right parenthesis, or 24 period 5 b equals 122 period 5. Dividing both sides of this equationby 24.5 yields b equals 5. Thus, 5 pints of blackberries are inthis purchase.\nChoices A and B are incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors. Choice D is incorrect. This is the number of pints of raspberries, not blackberries, in the purchase."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-189", "text": "One gallon of paint will cover 220 square feet of a surface. A room has a total wall area of w square feet. Which equation represents the total amount of paint upper P, in gallons, needed to paint the walls of the room twice?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["upper P equals StartFraction w Over 110 EndFraction", "upper P equals 440 w", "upper P equals StartFraction w Over 220 EndFraction", "upper P equals 220 w"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. It''s given that w represents the total wall area, in square feet. Since the walls 