 or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-226", "text": "The cost of renting a backhoe for up to 10 days is dollar sign 270 for the first day and dollar sign 135 for each additional day. Which of the following equations gives the cost y, in dollars, of renting the backhoe for x days, where x is a positive integer and x less than or equals 10?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["y equals 270 x minus 135", "y equals 270 x plus 135", "y equals 135 x plus 270", "y equals 135 x plus 135"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. It''s given that the cost of renting a backhoe for up to 10 days is dollar sign 270 for the first day and dollar sign 135 for each additional day. Therefore, the cost y, in dollars, for x days, where x less than or equals 10, is the sum of the cost for the first day, dollar sign 270, and the cost for the additional x minus 1 days, dollar sign 135 left parenthesis x minus 1 right parenthesis. It follows that y equals 270 plus 135 left parenthesis x minus 1 right parenthesis, which is equivalent to y equals 270 plus 135 x minus 135, or y equals 135 x plus 135.\nChoice A is incorrect. This equation represents a situation where the cost of renting a backhoe is dollar sign 135 for the first day and dollar sign 270 for each additional day.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-228", "text": "A certain town has an area of 4.36 square miles. What is the area, in square yards, of this town? left parenthesis 1 mile equals 1,760 yards right parenthesis", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["404", "7,674", "710,459", "13,505,536"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. Since the number of yards in 1 mile is 1,760, the number of square yards in 1 square mile is left parenthesis 1,760 right parenthesis left parenthesis 1,760 right parenthesis equals 3,097,600. Therefore, if the area of the town is 4.36 square miles, it is 4.36 left parenthesis 3,097,600 right parenthesis equals 13,505,536, in square yards.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from dividing the number of yards in a mile by the square mileage of the town.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from multiplying the number of yards in a mile by the square mileage of the town.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from dividing the number of square yards in a square mile by the square mileage of the town."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-232", "text": "minus 3 x plus 21 p x equals 84\nIn the given equation, p is a constant. The equation has no solution. What is the value of p?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["0", "one seventh", "four thirds", "4"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. A linear equation in one variable has no solution if and only if the equation is false; that is, when there is no value of x that produces a true statement. It''s given that in the equation minus 3 x plus 21 p x equals 84, p is a constant and the equation has no solution for x. Therefore, the value of the constant p is one that results in a false equation. Factoring out the common factor of minus 3 x on the left-hand side of the given equation yields minus 3 x left parenthesis 1 minus 7 p right parenthesis equals 84. Dividing both sides of this equation by negative 3 yields x left parenthesis 1 minus 7 p right parenthesis equals negative 28. Dividing both sides of this equation by left parenthesis 1 minus 7 p right parenthesis yields x equals StartFraction negative 28 Over 1 minus 7 p EndFraction. This equation is false if and only if 1 minus 7 p equals 0. Adding 7 p to both sides of 1 minus 7 p equals 0 yields 1 equals 7 p. Dividing both sides of this equation by 7 yields one seventh equals p. It follows that the equation x equals StartFraction negative 28 Over 1 minus 7 p EndFraction is false if and only if p equals one seventh. Therefore, the given equation has no solution if and only if the value of p is one seventh.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-233", "text": "StartFraction 14 x Over 7 y EndFraction equals 2 StartRoot w plus 19 EndRoot\nThe given equation relates the distinct positive real numbers w, x, and y. Which equation correctly expresses w in terms of x and y?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["w equals StartRoot StartFraction x Over y EndFraction EndRoot minus 19", "w equals StartRoot StartFraction 28 x Over 14 y EndFraction EndRoot minus 19", "w equals left parenthesis StartFraction x Over y EndFraction right parenthesis squared minus 19", "w equals left parenthesis StartFraction 28 x Over 14 y EndFraction right parenthesis squared minus 19"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. Dividing each side of the given equation by 2 yields StartFraction 14 x Over 14 y EndFraction equals StartFraction 2 StartRoot w plus 19 EndRoot Over 2 EndFraction, or StartFraction x Over y EndFraction equals StartRoot w plus 19 EndRoot. Because it''s given that each of the variables is positive, squaring each side of this equation yields the equivalent equation left parenthesis StartFraction x Over y EndFraction right parenthesis squared equals w plus 19. Subtracting 19 from each side of this equation yields left parenthesis StartFraction x Over y EndFraction right parenthesis squared minus 19 equals w, or w equals left parenthesis StartFraction x Over y EndFraction right parenthesis squared minus 19.\nChoice A is incorrect. This equation isn''t equivalent to the given equation. \nChoice B is incorrect. This equation isn''t equivalent to the given equation. \nChoice D is incorrect. This equation isn''t equivalent to the given equation."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-234", "text": "Data set F consists of 55 integers between 170 and 290. Data set G consists of all the integers in data set F as well as the integer 10. Which of the following must be less for data set F than for data set G?\n\nThe mean\nThe median", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["I only", "II only", "I and II", "Neither I nor II"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. It''s given that data set F consists of 55 integers between 170 and 290 and data set G consists of all the integers in data set F as well as the integer 10. Since the integer 10 is less than all the integers in data set F, the mean of data set G must be less than the mean of data set F. Thus, the mean of data set F isn''t less than the mean of data set G. When a data set is in ascending order, the median is between the two middle values when there is an even number of values and the median is the middle value when there is an odd number of values. It follows that the median of data set F is either greater than or equal to the median of data set G. Therefore, the median of data set F isn''t less than the median of data set G. Thus, neither the mean nor the median must be less for data set F than for data set G.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-235", "text": "StartFraction x squared Over StartRoot x squared minus c squared EndRoot EndFraction equals StartFraction c squared Over StartRoot x squared minus c squared EndRoot EndFraction plus 39\nIn the given equation, c is a positive constant. Which of the following is one of the solutions to the given equation?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["negative c", "minus c squared minus 39 squared", "minus StartRoot 39 squared minus c squared EndRoot", "minus StartRoot c squared plus 39 squared EndRoot"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. If x squared minus c squared less than or equals 0, then neither side of the given equation is defined and there can be no solution. Therefore, x squared minus c squared greater than 0. Subtracting StartFraction c squared Over StartRoot x squared minus c squared EndRoot EndFraction from both sides of the given equation yields StartFraction x squared Over StartRoot x squared minus c squared EndRoot EndFraction minus StartFraction c squared Over StartRoot x squared minus c squared EndRoot EndFraction equals 39, or StartFraction x squared minus c squared Over StartRoot x squared minus c squared EndRoot EndFraction equals 39. Squaring both sides of this equation yields left parenthesis StartFraction x squared minus c squared Over StartRoot x squared minus c squared EndRoot EndFraction right parenthesis squared equals 39 squared, or StartFraction left parenthesis x squared minus c squared right parenthesis left parenthesis x squared minus c squared right parenthesis Over x squared minus c squared EndFraction equals 39 squared. Since x squared minus c squared is positive and, therefore, nonzero, the expression StartFraction x squared minus c squared Over x squared minus c squared EndFraction is defined and equivalent to 1. It follows that the equation StartFraction left parenthesis x squared minus c squared right parenthesis left parenthesis x squared minus c squared right parenthesis Over x squared minus c squared EndFraction equals 39 squared can be rewritten as left parenthesis StartFraction x squared minus c squared Over x squared minus c squared EndFraction right parenthesis left parenthesis x squared minus c squared right parenthesis equals 39 squared, or left parenthesis 1 right parenthesis left parenthesis x squared minus c squared right parenthesis equals 39 squared, which is equivalent to x squared minus c squared equals 39 squared. Adding c squared to both sides of this equation yields x squared equals c squared plus 39 squared. Taking the square root of both sides of this equation yields two solutions: x equals StartRoot c squared plus 39 squared EndRoot and x equals minus StartRoot c squared plus 39 squared EndRoot. Therefore, of the given choices, minus StartRoot c squared plus 39 squared EndRoot is one of the solutions to the given equation.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-237", "text": "A quadratic function models a projectile''s height, in meters, above the ground in terms of the time, in seconds, after it was launched. The model estimates that the projectile was launched from an initial height of 7 meters above the ground and reached a maximum height of 51.1 meters above the ground 3 seconds after the launch. How many seconds after the launch does the model estimate that the projectile will return to a height of 7 meters?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["3", "6", "7", "9"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. It''s given that a quadratic function models the projectile''s height, in meters, above the ground in terms of the time, in seconds, after it was launched. It follows that an equation representing the model can be written in the form f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals a left parenthesis x minus h right parenthesis squared plus k, where f left parenthesis x right parenthesis is the projectile''s estimated height above the ground, in meters, x seconds after the launch, a is a constant, and k is the maximum height above the ground, in meters, the model estimates the projectile reached h seconds after the launch. It''s given that the model estimates the projectile reached a maximum height of 51.1 meters above the ground 3 seconds after the launch. Therefore, k equals 51.1 and h equals 3. Substituting 51.1 for k and 3 for h in the equation f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals a left parenthesis x minus h right parenthesis squared plus k yields f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals a left parenthesis x minus 3 right parenthesis squared plus 51.1. It''s also given that the model estimates that the projectile was launched from an initial height of 7 meters above the ground. Therefore, when x equals 0, f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 7. Substituting 0 for x and 7 for f left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the equation f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals a left parenthesis x minus 3 right parenthesis squared plus 51.1 yields 7 equals a left parenthesis 0 minus 3 right parenthesis squared plus 51.1, or 7 equals 9 a plus 51.1. Subtracting 51.1 from both sides of this equation yields negative 44.1 equals 9 a. Dividing both sides of this equation by 9 yields negative 4.9 equals a. Substituting negative 4.9 for a in the equation f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals a left parenthesis x minus 3 right parenthesis squared plus 51.1 yields f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals minus 4.9 left parenthesis x minus 3 right parenthesis squared plus 51.1. Therefore, the equation f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals minus 4.9 left parenthesis x minus 3 right parenthesis squared plus 51.1 models the projectile''s height, in meters, above the ground x seconds after it was launched. The number of seconds after the launch that the model estimates that the projectile will return to a height of 7 meters is the value of x when f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 7. Substituting 7 for f left parenthesis x right parenthesis in f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals minus 4.9 left parenthesis x minus 3 right parenthesis squared plus 51.1 yields 7 equals minus 4.9 left parenthesis x minus 3 right parenthesis squared plus 51.1. Subtracting 51.1 from both sides of this equation yields negative 44.1 equals minus 4.9 left parenthesis x minus 3 right parenthesis squared. Dividing both sides of this equation by negative 4.9 yields 9 equals left parenthesis x minus 3 right parenthesis squared. Taking the square root of both sides of this equation yields two equations: 3 equals x minus 3 and negative 3 equals x minus 3. Adding 3 to both sides of the equation 3 equals x minus 3 yields 6 equals x. Adding 3 to both sides of the equation negative 3 equals x minus 3 yields 0 equals x. Since 0 seconds after the launch represents the time at which the projectile was launched, 6 must be the number of seconds the model estimates that the projectile will return to a height of 7 meters.\nAlternate approach: It''s given that a quadratic function models the projectile''s height, in meters, above the ground in terms of the time, in seconds, after it was launched. It''s also given that the model estimates that the projectile was launched from an initial height of 7 meters above the ground and reached a maximum height of 51.1 meters above the ground 3 seconds after the launch. Since the model is quadratic, and quadratic functions are symmetric, the model estimates that for any given height less than the maximum height, the time the projectile takes to travel from the given height to the maximum height is the same as the time the projectile takes to travel from the maximum height back to the given height. Thus, since the model estimates the projectile took 3 seconds to travel from 7 meters above the ground to its maximum height of 51.1 meters above the ground, the model also estimates the projectile will take 3 more seconds to travel from its maximum height of 51.1 meters above the ground back to 7 meters above the ground. Thus, the model estimates that the projectile will return to a height of 7 meters 3 seconds after it reaches its maximum height, which is 6 seconds after the launch.\nChoice A is incorrect. The model estimates that 3 seconds after the launch, the projectile reached a height of 51.1 meters, not 7 meters.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-245", "text": "A window repair specialist charges dollar sign 220 for the first two hours of repair plus an hourly fee for each additional hour. The total cost for 5 hours of repair is dollar sign 400. Which function f gives the total cost, in dollars, for x hours of repair, where x greater than or equals 2?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 60 x plus 100", "f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 60 x plus 220", "f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 80 x", "f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 80 x plus 220"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. It\u2019s given that the window repair specialist charges dollar sign 220 for the first two hours of repair plus an hourly fee for each additional hour. Let n represent the hourly fee for each additional hour after the first two hours. Since it\u2019s given that x is the number of hours of repair, it follows that the charge generated by the hourly fee after the first two hours can be represented by the expression n left parenthesis x minus 2 right parenthesis. Therefore, the total cost, in dollars, for x hours of repair is f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 220 plus n left parenthesis x minus 2 right parenthesis. It\u2019s given that the total cost for 5 hours of repair is dollar sign 400. Substituting 5 for x and 400 for f left parenthesis x right parenthesis into the equation f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 220 plus n left parenthesis x minus 2 right parenthesis yields 400 equals 220 plus n left parenthesis 5 minus 2 right parenthesis, or 400 equals 220 plus 3 n. Subtracting 220 from both sides of this equation yields 180 equals 3 n. Dividing both sides of this equation by 3 yields n equals 60. Substituting 60 for n in the equation f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 220 plus n left parenthesis x minus 2 right parenthesis yields f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 220 plus 60 left parenthesis x minus 2 right parenthesis, which is equivalent to f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 220 plus 60 x minus 120, or f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 60 x plus 100. Therefore, the total cost, in dollars, for x hours of repair is f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 60 x plus 100.\nChoice B is incorrect. This function represents the total cost, in dollars, for x hours of repair where the specialist charges dollar sign 340, rather than dollar sign 220, for the first two hours of repair.\nChoice C is incorrect. This function represents the total cost, in dollars, for x hours of repair where the specialist charges dollar sign 160, rather than dollar sign 220, for the first two hours of repair, and an hourly fee of dollar sign 80, rather than dollar sign 60, after the first two hours.\nChoice D is incorrect. This function represents the total cost, in dollars, for x hours of repair where the specialist charges dollar sign 380, rather than dollar sign 220, for the first two hours of repair, and an hourly fee of dollar sign 80, rather than dollar sign 60, after the first two hours."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-247", "text": "The first term of a sequence is 9. Each term after the first is 4 times the preceding term. If w represents the nth term of the sequence, which equation gives w in terms of n?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["w equals 4 left parenthesis 9 Superscript n Baseline right parenthesis", "w equals 4 left parenthesis 9 Superscript n minus 1 Baseline right parenthesis", "w equals 9 left parenthesis 4 Superscript n Baseline right parenthesis", "w equals 9 left parenthesis 4 Superscript n minus 1 Baseline right parenthesis"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. Since w represents the nth term of the sequence and 9 is the first term of the sequence, the value of w is 9 when the value of n is 1. Since each term after the first is 4 times the preceding term, the value of w is 9 left parenthesis 4 right parenthesis when the value of n is 2. Therefore, the value of w is 9 left parenthesis 4 right parenthesis left parenthesis 4 right parenthesis, or 9 left parenthesis 4 right parenthesis squared, when the value of n is 3. More generally, the value of w is 9 left parenthesis 4 Superscript n minus 1 Baseline right parenthesis for a given value of n. Therefore, the equation w equals 9 left parenthesis 4 Superscript n minus 1 Baseline right parenthesis gives w in terms of n.\nChoice A is incorrect. This equation describes a sequence for which the first term is 36, rather than 9, and each term after the first is 9, rather than 4, times the preceding term. \nChoice B is incorrect. This equation describes a sequence for which the first term is 4, rather than 9, and each term after the first is 9, rather than 4, times the preceding term.\nChoice C is incorrect. This equation describes a sequence for which the first term is 36, rather than 9."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-250", "text": "In a study of cell phone use, 799 randomly selected US teens were asked how often they talked on a cell phone and about their texting behavior. The data are summarized in the table above. Based on the data from the study, an estimate of the percent of US teens who are heavy texters is 30% and the associated margin of error is 3%. Which of the following is a correct statement based on the given margin of error?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["Approximately 3% of the teens in the study who are classified as heavy texters are not really heavy texters.", "It is not possible that the percent of all US teens who are heavy texters is less than 27%.", "The percent of all US teens who are heavy texters is 33%.", "It is doubtful that the percent of all US teens who are heavy texters is 35%."], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. The given margin of error of 3% indicates that the actual percent of all US teens who are heavy texters is likely within 3% of the estimate of 30%, or between 27% and 33%. Therefore, it is unlikely, or doubtful, that the percent of all US teens who are heavy texters would be 35%.Choice A is incorrect. The margin of error doesn\u2019t provide any information about the accuracy of reporting in the study. Choice B is incorrect. Based on the estimate and given margin of error, it is unlikely that the percent of all US teens who are heavy texters would be less than 27%, but it is possible. Choice C is incorrect. While the percent of all US teens who are heavy texters is likely between 27% and 33%, any value within this interval is equally likely. We can\u2019t be certain that the value is exactly 33%."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-251", "text": "f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals left parenthesis x minus 10 right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus 13 right parenthesis\nThe function f is defined by the given equation. For what value of x does f left parenthesis x right parenthesis reach its minimum?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "secti