ession is equal to 3,136, not 392, times the volume of the cylinder shown.\nChoice D is incorrect. Substituting 49 r for upper R and 8 h for upper H in the expression that represents the volume of the second cylinder yields pi left parenthesis 49 r right parenthesis squared left parenthesis 8 h right parenthesis, or pi left parenthesis 2,401 r squared right parenthesis left parenthesis 8 h right parenthesis, which is equivalent to pi left parenthesis 19,208 r squared h right parenthesis, or 19,208 left parenthesis pi r squared h right parenthesis. This expression is equal to 19,208, not 392, times the volume of the cylinder shown."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-275", "text": "In the xy-plane, the graph of the equation y equals minus x squared plus 9 x minus 100 intersects the line y equals c at exactly one point. What is the value of c?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["negative StartFraction 481 Over 4 EndFraction", "negative 100", "negative StartFraction 319 Over 4 EndFraction", "negative nine halves"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. In the xy-plane, the graph of the line y equals c is a horizontal line that crosses the y-axis at y equals c and the graph of the quadratic equation y equals minus x squared plus 9 x minus 100 is a parabola. A parabola can intersect a horizontal line at exactly one point only at its vertex. Therefore, the value of c should be equal to the y-coordinate of the vertex of the graph of the given equation. For a quadratic equation in vertex form, y equals a left parenthesis x minus h right parenthesis squared plus k, the vertex of its graph in the xy-plane is left parenthesis h comma k right parenthesis. The given quadratic equation, y equals minus x squared plus 9 x minus 100, can be rewritten as y equals minus left parenthesis x squared minus 2 left parenthesis nine halves right parenthesis x plus left parenthesis nine halves right parenthesis squa