.8 right parenthesis squared plus 51.84. Therefore, h equals minus 16 left parenthesis t minus 1.8 right parenthesis squared plus 51.84 represents the height above ground h, in meters, of this softball t seconds after it is launched.\nChoice A is incorrect. This equation represents a situation where the maximum height is 3.6 meters above the ground at 0 seconds, not 51.84 meters above the ground at 1.8 seconds.\nChoice B is incorrect. This equation represents a situation where the maximum height is 51.84 meters above the ground at 0 seconds, not 1.8 seconds.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-298", "text": "y equals 6 x plus 18\nOne of the equations in a system of two linear equations is given. The system has no solution. Which equation could be the second equation in the system?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["minus 6 x plus y equals 18", "minus 6 x plus y equals 22", "minus 12 x plus y equals 36", "minus 12 x plus y equals 18"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. A system of two linear equations in two variables, x and y, has no solution if the lines represented by the equations in the xy-plane are parallel and distinct. Lines represented by equations in standard form, upper A x plus upper B y equals upper C and upper D x plus upper E y equals upper F, are parallel if the coefficients for x and y in one equation are proportional to the corresponding coefficients in the other equation, meaning StartFraction upper D Over upper A EndFraction equals StartFraction upper E Over upper B EndFraction; and the lines are distinct if the constants are not proportional, meaning StartFraction upper F Over upper C EndFraction is not equal to StartFraction upper D Over upper A EndFraction or StartFraction upper E Over upper B EndFraction. The given equation, y equals 6 x plus 18, can be written in standard form by subtr