 a bachelor\u2019s degree or higher for these 7 states and the median for all 50 states?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["0.05%", "0.95%", "1.22%", "7.45%"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. The median of a set of numbers is the middle value of the set values when ordered from least to greatest. If the percents in the table are ordered from least to greatest, the middle value is 27.9%. The difference between 27.9% and 26.95% is 0.95%.Choice A is incorrect and may be the result of calculation errors or not finding the median of the data in the table correctly. Choice C is incorrect and may be the result of finding the mean instead of the median. Choice D is incorrect and may be the result of using the middle value of the unordered list."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-389", "text": "x squared minus 40 x minus 10 equals 0\nWhat is the sum of the solutions to the given equation?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["0", "5", "10", "40"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. Adding 10 to each side of the given equation yields x squared minus 40 x equals 10. To complete the square, adding left parenthesis StartFraction 40 Over 2 EndFraction right parenthesis squared, or 20 squared, to each side of this equation yields x squared minus 40 x plus 20 squared equals 10 plus 20 squared, or left parenthesis x minus 20 right parenthesis squared equals 410. Taking the square root of each side of this equation yields x minus 20 equals plus or minus StartRoot 410 EndRoot. Adding 20 to each side of this equation yields x equals 20 plus or minus StartRoot 410 EndRoot. Therefore, the solutions to the given equation are x equals 20 plus StartRoot 410 EndRoot and x equals 20 minus StartRoot 410 EndRoot. The sum of these solutions is left parenthesis 20 plus StartRoot 410 EndRoot right parenthesis plus left parenthe