per D upper C is 90 degree. It follows that angle upper B is congruent to angle upper D and angle upper C is congruent to angle upper C. By the angle-angle similarity postulate, triangle upper A upper B upper C is similar to triangle upper B upper D upper C. Since triangles upper A upper B upper C and upper B upper D upper C are similar, it follows that StartFraction upper A upper C Over upper A upper B EndFraction equals StartFraction upper B upper C Over upper B upper D EndFraction. It''s also given that the length of line segment upper A upper B is 15 and the length of line segment upper A upper C is 23 greater than the length of line segment upper A upper B. Therefore, the length of line segment upper A upper C is 15 plus 23, or 38. Substituting 15 for upper A upper B and 38 for upper A upper C in the equation StartFraction upper A upper C Over upper A upper B EndFraction equals StartFraction upper B upper C Over upper B upper D EndFraction yields StartFraction 38 Over 15 EndFraction equals StartFraction upper B upper C Over upper B upper D EndFraction. Therefore, the value of StartFraction upper B upper C Over upper B upper D EndFraction is StartFraction 38 Over 15 EndFraction.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the value of StartFraction upper B upper D Over upper B upper C EndFraction.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-415", "text": "If StartFraction x plus 6 Over 3 EndFraction equals StartFraction x plus 6 Over 13 EndFraction, the value of x plus 6 is between which of the following pairs of values?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["negative 7 and negative 3", "negative 2 and 2", "2 and 7", "8 and 13"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. Multiplying both sides of the given equation by left parenthesis 3 right parenthesis left parenthesis 13 right parenthesis, or 39, yields left parenthesis 39 right parenthesis left parenthesis StartFraction x plus 6 Over 3 EndFraction right parenthesis equals left parenthesis 39 right parenthesis left parenthesis StartFraction x plus 6 Over 13 EndFraction right parenthesis, or 13 left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis equals 3 left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis. Subtracting 3 left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis from both sides of this equation yields 10 left parenthesis x plus 6 right parenthesis equals 0. Dividing both sides of this equation by 10 yields x plus 6 equals 0. Therefore, if StartFraction x plus 6 Over 3 EndFraction equals StartFraction x plus 6 Over 13 EndFraction, then the value of x plus 6 is 0. It follows that of the given choices, the value of x plus 6 is between negative 2 and 2.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}]'::jsonb);
INSERT INTO sat_tests (title, description, test_type, difficulty, length, section, is_official, time_limit_minutes, questions) VALUES ('OpenSAT Math - Hard Set 5','Official-style SAT Math practice (Hard) from OpenSAT — image-free questions only.','math','hard','medium','math',true,38,'[{"id": "opensat-math-mcq-417", "text": "A model estimates that at the end of each year from 2015 to 2020, the number of squirrels in a population was 150 percent sign more than the number of squirrels in the population at the end of the previous year. The model estimates that at the end of 2016, there were 180 squirrels in the population. Which of the following equations represents this model, where n is the estimated number of squirrels in the population t years after the end of 2015 and t less than or equals 5?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["n equals 72 left parenthesis 1.5 right parenthesis Superscript t", "n equals 72 left parenthesis 2.5 right parenthesis Superscript t", "n equals 180 left parenthesis 1.5 right parenthesis Superscript t", "n equals 180 left parenthesis 2.5 right parenthesis Superscript t"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. Since the model estimates that the number of squirrels in the population increased by a fixed percentage, 150 percent sign, each year, the model can be represented by an exponential equation of the form n equals a left parenthesis 1 plus StartFraction p Over 100 EndFraction right parenthesis Superscript t, where a is the estimated number of squirrels in the population at the end of 2015, and the model estimates that at the end of each year, the number is p percent sign more than the number at the end of the previous year. Since the model estimates that at the end of each year, the number was 150 percent sign more than the number at the end of the previous year, p equals 150. Substituting 150 for p in the equation n equals a left parenthesis 1 plus StartFraction p Over 100 EndFraction right parenthesis Superscript t yields n equals a left parenthesis 1 plus StartFraction 150 Over 100 EndFraction right parenthesis Superscript t, which is equivalent to n equals a left parenthesis 1 plus 1.5 right parenthesis Superscript t, or n equals a left parenthesis 2.5 right parenthesis Superscript t. It\u2019s given that the estimated number of squirrels at the end of 2016 was 180. This means that when t equals 1, n equals 180. Substituting 1 for t and 180 for n in the equation n equals a left parenthesis 2.5 right parenthesis Superscript t yields 180 equals a left parenthesis 2.5 right parenthesis Superscript 1, or 180 equals 2.5 a. Dividing each side of this equation by 2.5 yields 72 equals a. Substituting 72 for a in the equation n equals a left parenthesis 2.5 right parenthesis Superscript t yields n equals 72 left parenthesis 2.5 right parenthesis Superscript t.\nChoice A is incorrect. This equation represents a model where at the end of each year, the estimated number of squirrels was 150 percent sign of, not 150 percent sign more than, the estimated number at the end of the previous year.\nChoice C is incorrect. This equation represents a model where at the end of each year, the estimated number of squirrels was 150 percent sign of, not 150 percent sign more than, the estimated number at the end of the previous year, and the estimated number of squirrels at the end of 2015, not the end of 2016, was 180.\nChoice D is incorrect. This equation represents a model where the estimated number of squirrels at the end of 2015, not the end of 2016, was 180."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-419", "text": "x squared minus 2 x minus 9 equals 0\nOne solution to the given equation can be written as 1 plus StartRoot k EndRoot, where k is a constant. What is the value of k?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["8", "10", "20", "40"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "hard", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. Adding 9 to each side of the given equation yields x squared minus 2 x equals 9. To complete the square, adding 1 to each side of this equation yields x squared minus 2 x plus 1 equals 9 plus 1, or left parenthesis x minus 1 right parenthesis squared equals 10. Taking the square root of each side of this equation yields x minus 1 equals plus or minus StartRoot 10 EndRoot. Adding 1 to each side of this equation yields x equals 1 plus or minus StartRoot 10 EndRoot. Since it''s given that one of the solutions to the equation can be written as 1 plus StartRoot k EndRoot, the value of k must be 10.\nAlternate approach: It''s given that 1 plus StartRoot k EndRoot is a solution to the given equation. It follows that x equals 1 plus StartRoot k EndRoot. Substituting 1 plus StartRoot k EndRoot for x in the given equation yields left parenthesis 1 plus StartRoot k EndRoot right parenthesis squared minus 2 left parenthesis 1 plus StartRoot k EndRoot right parenthesis minus 9 equals 0, or left parenthesis 1 plus StartRoot k EndRoot right parenthesis left parenthesis 1 plus StartRoot k EndRoot right parenthesis minus 2 left parenthesis 1 plus StartRoot k EndRoot right parenthesis minus 9 equals 0. Expanding the products on the left-hand side of this equation yields 1 plus 2 StartRoot k EndRoot plus k minus 2 minus 2 StartRoot k EndRoot minus 9 equals 0, or k minus 10 equals 0. Adding 10 to each side of this equation yields k equals 10.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-420", "text": "Near the end of a US cable news show, the host invited viewers to respond to a poll on the show\u2019s website that asked, \u201cDo you support the new federal policy discussed during the show?\u201d At the end of the show, the host reported that 28% responded \u2